  <prompt>
    Define the canonical `WorkspaceTab` TypeScript interface that becomes the contract
    shared by Pillars 6a (state model), 6b (chat tools that mutate tabs), 6c (workspace
    events), 7 (memory composition reads tab content), and 9 (visibility contract per-tab
    filter). This task ships interfaces only ‚Äî no implementation. Required typed fields:
    `id`, `widgetType` (string enum union), `widgetData` (per-widget-type discriminated
    union), `sessionId`, `visibleToAssistant: boolean`, `sourceProvenance` (which
    playbook/agent/user created it + when), `matterContext` (matterId + matter name),
    `isPinned: boolean`, `canEdit: boolean`, `lastUserEditAt?: string` (ISO-8601;
    central to Q8 conflict resolution), `createdAt`, `updatedAt`. Place in
    `@spaarke/ai-widgets` shared library (NOT a code-page). Export from package index so
    Pillar 6b chat tools, Pillar 7 memory composition, and Pillar 9 visibility contract
    can import the canonical shape.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior TypeScript engineer with deep familiarity with the Spaarke `@spaarke/ai-widgets`
    package + PaneEventBus discriminated-union typing patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A single `WorkspaceTab` interface lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets/src/types/` and is
    exported from the package barrel. All typed fields are documented with JSDoc citing
    the originating FR (FR-31). The shape supports discriminated unions across widget
    types (Summary, DocumentViewer, Dashboard, Table). Pillars 6b/6c/7/9 task authors can
    import this interface without ambiguity. Type-check passes across the package.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
